 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-16: Session-phase-aware strategy selection — override k_eff strategy for orientation phase (ADR-BUDGET-007, INV-REFLEXIVE-002). BACKGROUND: AUDIT ISSUE 7. The ActivationStrategy is based on k_eff alone, but from prompt-optimization theory, early turns (1-5) should ALWAYS use Demonstrate regardless of k_eff — this is the trajectory-seeding phase where investment in rich context pays exponential dividends. The session-phase signal comes from tx count since session start (turn proxy): turns 1-5 = Orientation (always Demonstrate), turns 5-20 = ActiveWork (k_eff-based), turns 20-40 = ContextPressure (k_eff-based but biased toward Navigate), turns 40+ = HarvestZone (biased toward Signal). APPROACH: (1) Add SessionPhase enum: Orientation, ActiveWork, ContextPressure, HarvestZone. (2) Add session_phase(tx_since_session: usize) -> SessionPhase. (3) Modify strategy selection: strategy_for_context(k_eff: f64, phase: SessionPhase) -> ActivationStrategy. Phase overrides: Orientation always returns Demonstrate, HarvestZone caps at Navigate. (4) tx_since_session comes from the existing tx_velocity infrastructure in guidance.rs. Tests: (A) At tx_count=0, strategy is always Demonstrate regardless of k_eff. (B) At tx_count=30 with k_eff=0.5, strategy is Navigate. (C) At tx_count=50 with k_eff=0.8, strategy is capped at Navigate (not Demonstrate). (D) Phase transitions are monotonic (Orientation -> ActiveWork -> ... -> HarvestZone). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/budget.rs"
